<TITLE> Budget speech starts at 3pm Thursday on radio, TV stations </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 5 (bdnews24.com) - Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam will announce the fiscal 2007-08 budget at 3pm Thursday on radio and television stations, the government has said in a statement. Documents including budget speech, summary of the budget and annual financial statement will be webcast on the finance ministry's website: www.mof.gv.bd. To ensure extensive participation of people, budget documents will be available on some other government websites: www.bangladesh.gov.bd, www.nbr-bd.org, www,plancomm.gov.bd, www.imed.gov.bd, www.bdpressinform.org and www.cao.gov.bd. The statement released by the Press Information Department said an individual or an organisation could download budget documents from any of the websites. The websites will be open to comments on the budget until 5pm of June 14. The budget will be finalised by a presidential ordinance, it said. bd
